President Donald J. Trump's summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un in Singapore has been hailed as a historic moment and a step towards peace on the Korean Peninsula. The two leaders signed a document that commits North Korea to "complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula," which was a key requirement for the U.S. The summit has been praised as a bold move by Trump to engage with Kim and has been seen as a positive step towards peace. However, critics are cautious and point out that North Korea has made similar promises in the past without following through. Overall, the summit is seen as a positive development, but the success of the agreement will depend on future actions and negotiations.